1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,272
Welcome to The Unburdening Ceremony.

2
00:00:04,272 --> 00:00:13,237
This is a gentle visualization practice
for imagining what it might be like for a

3
00:00:13,237 --> 00:00:17,832
part to release something it has carried.

4
00:00:17,832 --> 00:00:22,383
Only do this if the part feels ready.

5
00:00:22,383 --> 00:00:25,587
Unburdening cannot be forced.

6
00:00:25,587 --> 00:00:35,247
If the part is not ready, this practice
can simply become a listening practice.

7
00:00:35,247 --> 00:00:39,798
Begin by settling your body.

8
00:00:39,798 --> 00:00:42,909
Take a slow breath in.

9
00:00:51,909 --> 00:00:51,909
<break time="3s" />

10
00:00:51,909 --> 00:00:54,370
And let it out.

11
00:00:54,370 --> 00:00:59,711
Bring to mind a part that has been
carrying something heavy.

12
00:00:59,711 --> 00:01:09,280
Maybe shame, fear, responsibility,
loneliness, guilt, a belief about itself,

13
00:01:09,280 --> 00:01:12,853
or a belief about the world.

14
00:01:12,853 --> 00:01:15,686
Notice this part gently.

15
00:01:15,686 --> 00:01:21,955
Ask: Is it okay for me to be with you
right now?

16
00:01:33,955 --> 00:01:33,955
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

17
00:01:33,955 --> 00:01:39,853
If the answer is no, thank the part for
letting you know.

18
00:01:39,853 --> 00:01:45,008
You can stop here or simply offer
presence.

19
00:01:45,008 --> 00:01:52,624
If the answer is yes, ask: What burden
have you been carrying?

20
00:02:04,624 --> 00:02:04,624
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

21
00:02:04,624 --> 00:02:07,875
Let the answer come slowly.

22
00:02:25,875 --> 00:02:25,875
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s"
/><break time="3s" />

23
00:02:25,875 --> 00:02:30,798
Now ask: How long have you been carrying
this?

24
00:02:42,798 --> 00:02:42,798
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

25
00:02:42,798 --> 00:02:46,931
And: Who or what gave this to you?

26
00:02:58,931 --> 00:02:58,931
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

27
00:02:58,931 --> 00:03:03,203
Listen without forcing details.

28
00:03:03,203 --> 00:03:10,989
Now ask: Do you want to keep carrying
this burden, or are you interested in

29
00:03:10,989 --> 00:03:15,092
imagining what release might feel like?

30
00:03:27,092 --> 00:03:27,092
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

31
00:03:27,092 --> 00:03:29,553
Respect the answer.

32
00:03:29,553 --> 00:03:37,819
If the part is not ready, say: I will not
force you. We can go slowly.

33
00:03:37,819 --> 00:03:45,389
If the part is ready, imagine a safe
place where release can happen.

34
00:03:57,389 --> 00:03:57,389
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

35
00:03:57,389 --> 00:04:07,498
Maybe near water, fire, earth, wind,
light, a sacred container, a field, or a

36
00:04:07,498 --> 00:04:08,163
tree.

37
00:04:08,163 --> 00:04:10,717
Let the part choose.

38
00:04:10,717 --> 00:04:16,011
Ask the part: How would you like to
release this burden?

39
00:04:28,011 --> 00:04:28,011
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

40
00:04:28,011 --> 00:04:35,563
It may place it in water, burn it safely
in fire, bury it in earth, let wind carry

41
00:04:35,563 --> 00:04:40,225
it, give it to light, set it down, or
transform it.

42
00:04:40,225 --> 00:04:43,801
Let the part choose the image.

43
00:04:43,801 --> 00:04:51,928
Now imagine the burden leaving the part
only at the pace that feels safe.

44
00:05:03,928 --> 00:05:03,928
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

45
00:05:03,928 --> 00:05:07,783
No rush. No force.

46
00:05:07,783 --> 00:05:11,127
The part remains in control.

47
00:05:11,127 --> 00:05:19,347
As the burden releases, ask: What do you
want to receive instead?

48
00:05:31,347 --> 00:05:31,347
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

49
00:05:31,347 --> 00:05:41,610
Maybe lightness, play, rest, worthiness,
protection, love, choice, or belonging.

50
00:05:41,610 --> 00:05:46,858
Let the part receive only what feels
welcome.

51
00:05:46,858 --> 00:05:56,192
Now notice how the part looks or feels
after releasing even a small amount.

52
00:06:14,192 --> 00:06:14,192
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s"
/><break time="3s" />

53
00:06:14,192 --> 00:06:22,923
Ask: What do you need from me so this
release can continue safely over time?

54
00:06:34,923 --> 00:06:34,923
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

55
00:06:34,923 --> 00:06:36,223
Listen.

56
00:06:54,223 --> 00:06:54,223
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s"
/><break time="3s" />

57
00:06:54,223 --> 00:07:01,997
Offer reassurance: I will not abandon you
after this. You do not have to change all

58
00:07:01,997 --> 00:07:05,694
at once. We can keep learning together.

59
00:07:05,694 --> 00:07:07,923
Now thank the part.

60
00:07:07,923 --> 00:07:14,657
Thank any protectors who allowed this
process.

61
00:07:14,657 --> 00:07:19,673
Thank your system for moving at its own
pace.

62
00:07:19,673 --> 00:07:23,992
Bring attention back to your body.

63
00:07:35,992 --> 00:07:35,992
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

64
00:07:35,992 --> 00:07:39,243
Feel the support beneath you.

65
00:07:51,243 --> 00:07:51,243
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

66
00:07:51,243 --> 00:07:53,844
Take a slow breath in.

67
00:08:02,844 --> 00:08:02,844
<break time="3s" />

68
00:08:02,844 --> 00:08:04,980
And let it out.

69
00:08:04,980 --> 00:08:07,813
Return gently to the room.

